    "updated_at": "2023-05-25T03:14:24Z",
    "body": "For anyone who finds this looking for something similar, I did write up a custom module, but due to the relative simplicity of it, I think it should be added to the base `git_state` module.\r\n\r\n`starship.toml`\r\n```toml\r\n[custom.git_am_state]\r\nwhen = \"git am --show-current-patch &>/dev/null\"\r\nrequire_repo = true\r\ncommand = \"$HOME/.scripts/starship/git_am_state_progress.sh\"\r\nstyle = \"bg:#FD9D72 fg:bright-red bold\"\r\nformat = \"[ $output]($style)\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n`$HOME/.scripts/starship/git_am_state_progress.sh`\r\n```bash\r\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\r\n\r\nGIT_DIR=$(git rev-parse --git-dir)\r\nNEXT=$(cat \"$GIT_DIR/rebase-apply/next\")\r\nLAST=$(cat \"$GIT_DIR/rebase-apply/last\")\r\n\r\necho \"$NEXT/$LAST\" | tr -d ' '\r\n```",
